Bia is...alright. The first time I came here, the food was okay, and the service was fine, too. But the second time, most of the beers were out, and the chicken curry soup I received was WAY too salty. It would've been a good soup, but it just seemed like they had added too much salt. I think I've sent back a dish twice before in my life, so I'm not just unbearably particular, this was not an edible soup. When I told them I wasn't satisfied by the soup, instead of offering to comp the dish and offer an alternative, the waitress instead took the soup back, tasted it with the rest of the kitchen, and insisted it was just fine and she didn't know what to do about it. To be fair, the kitchen was closing soon, and I know it can be stressful, but my friend and I just left hungry instead.  Otherwise, the grilled chicken banh mi was just fine, but the food here isn't spectacular in general, I don't really understand the hype, but the least you can do is offer good service if your food isn't up to par this one time.
